NOTE: median (p50) diff across all meta columns is at machine precision (~1e-11).
A handful of outlier cells (λ₀ ∈ {0, ≥0.75}) drive the tail of beta/SR diffs.
Root cause: sklearn `lars_path` vs R `lars` package differ in how they log
intra-step drops (coefficient crossing zero without changing support size).
The argmax-on-valid cell (i*, j*) is identical between Python and R regardless.

