IMPORTANT CAVEAT on R's 'ground-truth' non-grid files
------------------------------------------------------------------------
R's Selected_Ports_10.csv, Selected_Ports_Weights_10.csv, train/valid/test_SR_10.csv
and SDFTests/.../TimeSeriesAlpha.csv in the shared data dir were generated by
main_simplified.R at the single cell (λ₀=0.15, λ₂=1e-8) and were NOT regenerated
after main.R's full-grid run. We confirmed this by matching R's weight vector
byte-for-byte to grid cell (i=4, j=13) = (λ₀=0.15, λ₂=1e-8).

→ Comparing our *full-grid* Selected_Ports_10 against those files is apples-to-
  oranges; the cell chosen under the full grid is (0.75, 1e-8), not (0.15, 1e-8).
→ The 988 grid CSVs and SR_N.csv ARE from R's full-grid run and ARE comparable.
→ Sanity-check block below reruns pick_best_lambda at the single cell (0.15, 1e-8)
  and diffs against R's ground truth — expected to be machine precision.

